File: Residents are protesting over the removal of informal settlements in Lenasia and Lawley, JOHANNESBURG - Communities in Lenasia and Lawley in the south of Johannesburg have taken to the streets. Residents are protesting over the removal of informal settlements in the area. READ: KZN community demands water and electricity The protests apparently started on Monday morning. Roads were blocked with rocks and burning tyres. The red ants previously demolished shacks in the area prompting protests against the City of Johannesburg.